            . I am a painter. On the 30th of December, at half-past nine o'clock, I saw the prisoner and another, near Mr. Pitmann's shop; I watched them. and saw the prisoner go into the shop, and take a pair of shoes from the right-hand side of the door - I told the shopman, who ran and took him with the shoes in his possession; he was brought back and given to the officer.</p>
               <p>WALTER PITMANN. I <rs id="t18290115-76-viclabel377" type="occupation">keep the shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-76-victim586 t18290115-76-viclabel377"></join>, but was out that night - when I came home my shopman told me of the circumstance; these shoes are mine.</p>
